Introduction

This package contains one function used from labs 6-10 in addition to a data set taken from the textbook.

First Function: Sampling

Dataset: None

MATH4753jeff0035::mybin(iter=1000,n=18, p=0.3)

This function creates a random sample based on the given parameters and places them into a matrix.

Second Function: NCurve

Dataset: None

MATH4753jeff0035::myncurve(mu = 5, sigma = 10, a = 7)

## $Area
## [1] 0.5792597

This function creates a normal curve and fills in the area between the curve and the x axis from x = a until x = negative infinity and provides this area.

Third Function: MyCLTU

Dataset: None

MATH4753jeff0035::mycltu(n=20,iter=100000)

This function uses the sample and creates a density plot of the mean values from that sample.

Fourth Function: MyBoot2

Dataset: None
